[
    {
        "text": "Hi, everybody.\nWelcome to this video.",
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 3.245
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, in this video, we’re going to talk\nabout subjective pronouns,",
        "start": 3.245,
        "duration": 5.218
    },
    {
        "text": "‘be’ verbs, and also, contractions.",
        "start": 8.463,
        "duration": 3.583
    },
    {
        "text": "So let’s take a look at the board.",
        "start": 12.046,
        "duration": 3.059
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.\nFirst, we have the subjective pronouns.",
        "start": 15.106,
        "duration": 4.671
    },
    {
        "text": "And we have the ‘be’ verbs: am, is, and are.",
        "start": 19.777,
        "duration": 6.04
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.\nSo let’s look at the first one.",
        "start": 25.817,
        "duration": 2.897
    },
    {
        "text": "“I am”.\n“I am Esther”.",
        "start": 28.714,
        "duration": 4.739
    },
    {
        "text": "The contraction for ‘I am’ is ‘I’m’.",
        "start": 33.453,
        "duration": 4.657
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m”.",
        "start": 38.11,
        "duration": 1.017
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, a contraction is a more common way of\nsaying subjective pronouns and their ‘be’ verb.",
        "start": 39.127,
        "duration": 7.721
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s faster and quicker and shorter.",
        "start": 46.848,
        "duration": 3.627
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay, it’s more common.",
        "start": 50.475,
        "duration": 1.616
    },
    {
        "text": "I want you to use contractions.\nOkay.",
        "start": 52.091,
        "duration": 4.647
    },
    {
        "text": "So, “I am” becomes “I’m”.",
        "start": 56.738,
        "duration": 4.438
    },
    {
        "text": "“He is” – “he’s”.",
        "start": 61.176,
        "duration": 4.8
    },
    {
        "text": "“She is” - “she’s”.",
        "start": 65.976,
        "duration": 3.993
    },
    {
        "text": "“It is” - “it’s”.",
        "start": 69.969,
        "duration": 3.571
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay, let’s move on to the bottom.",
        "start": 73.54,
        "duration": 2.218
    },
    {
        "text": "“You are” becomes “you’re”.",
        "start": 75.758,
        "duration": 3.819
    },
    {
        "text": "“You’re”.",
        "start": 79.577,
        "duration": 2.36
    },
    {
        "text": "“We are” – “we’re”.\n“We’re”.",
        "start": 81.937,
        "duration": 5.068
    },
    {
        "text": "and “They are”.\nThe contraction is “they’re”.",
        "start": 87.005,
        "duration": 4.988
    },
    {
        "text": "“They’re”.",
        "start": 91.993,
        "duration": 1.723
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay, let’s move on to the next part.",
        "start": 93.716,
        "duration": 3.309
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.",
        "start": 97.025,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "We’re going to take a look at some sentences\nusing the ‘be’ verbs.",
        "start": 97.526,
        "duration": 4.905
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, notice on the board, I only used contractions.",
        "start": 102.431,
        "duration": 4.562
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.",
        "start": 106.993,
        "duration": 0.869
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, instead of “I am”, I’m\ngoing to say “I’m”.",
        "start": 107.862,
        "duration": 4.657
    },
    {
        "text": "So, the first sentence.\n“I’m a student”.",
        "start": 112.519,
        "duration": 3.562
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.\nThis means one.",
        "start": 116.081,
        "duration": 2.418
    },
    {
        "text": "So we have to say, “a student”.",
        "start": 118.499,
        "duration": 2.989
    },
    {
        "text": "“a”",
        "start": 121.488,
        "duration": 1.088
    },
    {
        "text": "Now many people make the mistake of saying,",
        "start": 122.576,
        "duration": 2.95
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m student”, but that’s wrong.\nOkay.",
        "start": 125.526,
        "duration": 3.213
    },
    {
        "text": "You have to put ‘a’.",
        "start": 128.739,
        "duration": 2.021
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, before I read it, you have to listen carefully.",
        "start": 130.76,
        "duration": 3.913
    },
    {
        "text": "‘I’m a’  - sounds like one word.",
        "start": 134.673,
        "duration": 3.198
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m a…”\n“I’m a…”",
        "start": 137.871,
        "duration": 2.828
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m a student”.",
        "start": 140.699,
        "duration": 1.631
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.\nPlease repeat after me.",
        "start": 142.33,
        "duration": 2.679
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m a student”.\n“I’m a student”.",
        "start": 145.009,
        "duration": 4.579
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay, the next one, again, sounds like one word.",
        "start": 149.588,
        "duration": 2.697
    },
    {
        "text": "“He’s a…”.\n“He’s a…”.",
        "start": 152.285,
        "duration": 2.389
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.so…",
        "start": 154.674,
        "duration": 0.949
    },
    {
        "text": "“He’s a student”.",
        "start": 155.623,
        "duration": 1.543
    },
    {
        "text": "Please repeat.",
        "start": 157.166,
        "duration": 1.434
    },
    {
        "text": "“He’s a student”.\n“He’s a student”.",
        "start": 158.6,
        "duration": 4.581
    },
    {
        "text": "Same thing.",
        "start": 163.181,
        "duration": 1.156
    },
    {
        "text": "“She’s a student”.",
        "start": 164.337,
        "duration": 2.043
    },
    {
        "text": "Please repeat.",
        "start": 166.38,
        "duration": 1.228
    },
    {
        "text": "“She’s a student”.\n“She’s a student”.",
        "start": 167.608,
        "duration": 4.57
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.\nThe next sentence has ‘it’.",
        "start": 172.178,
        "duration": 3.183
    },
    {
        "text": "Now remember, ‘it’ is only used for a\nplace, a thing or an animal.",
        "start": 175.361,
        "duration": 5.262
    },
    {
        "text": "So we can’t have those things be a student.",
        "start": 180.623,
        "duration": 3.243
    },
    {
        "text": "So we have to say, “It’s a dog”.",
        "start": 183.866,
        "duration": 3.327
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay, please repeat.",
        "start": 187.193,
        "duration": 1.431
    },
    {
        "text": "“It’s a dog”.\n“It’s a dog”.",
        "start": 188.624,
        "duration": 3.968
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay, the next one.",
        "start": 192.592,
        "duration": 1.726
    },
    {
        "text": "“You’re a student”.",
        "start": 194.318,
        "duration": 2.319
    },
    {
        "text": "Please repeat.",
        "start": 196.638,
        "duration": 1.254
    },
    {
        "text": "“You’re a student”.\n“You’re a student”.",
        "start": 197.892,
        "duration": 5.1
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.\nNow let’s look at ‘we’re’.",
        "start": 202.992,
        "duration": 2.476
    },
    {
        "text": "“We’re students”.\nOkay.",
        "start": 205.468,
        "duration": 2.833
    },
    {
        "text": "We took out the ‘a’ and we put an ‘s’",
        "start": 208.302,
        "duration": 2.591
    },
    {
        "text": "because ‘we’re’ means many people.",
        "start": 210.893,
        "duration": 2.429
    },
    {
        "text": "Not one student, but many students.",
        "start": 213.322,
        "duration": 3.29
    },
    {
        "text": "So, we have to say, “we’re students”.",
        "start": 216.612,
        "duration": 3.556
    },
    {
        "text": "Please repeat.",
        "start": 220.168,
        "duration": 1.293
    },
    {
        "text": "“We’re students”.\n“We’re students”.",
        "start": 221.461,
        "duration": 5.35
    },
    {
        "text": "The same thing goes for ‘they’.",
        "start": 226.811,
        "duration": 2.472
    },
    {
        "text": "Again, ‘they’ means many people…or many things.",
        "start": 229.283,
        "duration": 3.249
    },
    {
        "text": "Here, we put ‘s’.\nAnd we took out the ‘a’.",
        "start": 232.532,
        "duration": 3.707
    },
    {
        "text": "So, “they’re students”.",
        "start": 236.239,
        "duration": 2.539
    },
    {
        "text": "Please repeat.",
        "start": 238.778,
        "duration": 1.148
    },
    {
        "text": "“They’re students”.\n“They’re students”.",
        "start": 239.926,
        "duration": 4.3
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay, we’re going to look at some more examples.",
        "start": 244.226,
        "duration": 3.048
    },
    {
        "text": "Please listen and repeat carefully.",
        "start": 247.275,
        "duration": 4.048
    },
    {
        "text": "Let’s start with the first one: “I’m”.",
        "start": 251.323,
        "duration": 3.969
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m a boy”.\n“I’m a boy”.",
        "start": 255.292,
        "duration": 5.043
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m a girl”.\n“I’m a girl”.",
        "start": 260.335,
        "duration": 5.147
    },
    {
        "text": "“He’s”.",
        "start": 265.482,
        "duration": 1.933
    },
    {
        "text": "“He’s a man”.\n“He’s a man”.",
        "start": 267.415,
        "duration": 5.346
    },
    {
        "text": "“He’s a boy”.\n“He’s a boy”.",
        "start": 272.761,
        "duration": 4.553
    },
    {
        "text": "“She’s”.",
        "start": 277.314,
        "duration": 1.997
    },
    {
        "text": "“She’s a woman”.\n“She’s a woman”.",
        "start": 279.311,
        "duration": 5.768
    },
    {
        "text": "“She’s a girl”.\n“She’s a girl”.",
        "start": 285.079,
        "duration": 5.131
    },
    {
        "text": "“It’s”.",
        "start": 290.21,
        "duration": 1.719
    },
    {
        "text": "“It’s a chair”.\n“It’s a chair”.",
        "start": 291.929,
        "duration": 5.638
    },
    {
        "text": "“It’s a cat”.\n“It’s a cat”.",
        "start": 297.567,
        "duration": 5.192
    },
    {
        "text": "“You’re”.",
        "start": 302.759,
        "duration": 2.255
    },
    {
        "text": "“You’re a singer”.\n“You’re a singer”.",
        "start": 305.014,
        "duration": 5.052
    },
    {
        "text": "“You’re a friend”.\n“You’re a friend”.",
        "start": 310.066,
        "duration": 5.1
    },
    {
        "text": "“We’re”.",
        "start": 315.166,
        "duration": 1.88
    },
    {
        "text": "“We’re sisters”.\n“We’re sisters”.",
        "start": 317.046,
        "duration": 5.942
    },
    {
        "text": "“We’re brothers”.\n“We’re brothers”.",
        "start": 322.988,
        "duration": 5.532
    },
    {
        "text": "“They’re”.",
        "start": 328.52,
        "duration": 2.038
    },
    {
        "text": "“They’re people”.\n“They’re people”.",
        "start": 330.558,
        "duration": 5.653
    },
    {
        "text": "“They’re cars”.\n“They’re cars”.",
        "start": 336.211,
        "duration": 6.245
    },
    {
        "text": "Well I hope that this video helped you understand",
        "start": 342.457,
        "duration": 3.334
    },
    {
        "text": "how to use subjective pronouns,",
        "start": 345.791,
        "duration": 2.719
    },
    {
        "text": "their ‘be’ verbs, and also contractions.",
        "start": 348.51,
        "duration": 3.536
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, before we go, I wanted to share a little bit about myself using the lesson.",
        "start": 352.046,
        "duration": 6.937
    },
    {
        "text": "So, first, remember, “I’m a…”.",
        "start": 358.983,
        "duration": 2.853
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m a girl”.",
        "start": 361.836,
        "duration": 2.732
    },
    {
        "text": "Also, “I’m a teacher”.",
        "start": 364.568,
        "duration": 4.186
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m an American”.",
        "start": 368.754,
        "duration": 2.443
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, the word ‘American’ starts with the vowel ‘a’,",
        "start": 371.197,
        "duration": 4.569
    },
    {
        "text": "so we have to say ‘an’.",
        "start": 375.766,
        "duration": 2.314
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m an American”.",
        "start": 378.08,
        "duration": 2.536
    },
    {
        "text": "And “I’m an animal lover”.",
        "start": 380.616,
        "duration": 2.695
    },
    {
        "text": "Again, same thing.",
        "start": 383.311,
        "duration": 1.658
    },
    {
        "text": "‘Animal’ starts with the vowel ‘a’,",
        "start": 384.969,
        "duration": 2.724
    },
    {
        "text": "so we have to put ‘an’.",
        "start": 387.693,
        "duration": 1.655
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m an animal lover”.",
        "start": 389.348,
        "duration": 1.579
    },
    {
        "text": "And that means someone who loves animals.",
        "start": 390.927,
        "duration": 3.268
    },
    {
        "text": "I love dogs and cats and other animals.",
        "start": 394.195,
        "duration": 3.035
    },
    {
        "text": "So, “I’m an animal lover”.",
        "start": 397.23,
        "duration": 2.204
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.",
        "start": 399.434,
        "duration": 0.871
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, that’s it and thank you for watching.",
        "start": 400.305,
        "duration": 1.999
    },
    {
        "text": "And I’ll see you guys next time.",
        "start": 402.304,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "Bye.",
        "start": 403.824,
        "duration": 1.664
    }
]